  "prompt": "What causes road rage?",
  "response": "Road rage is caused by several factors:\n\n1. Psychological factors\n- High stress levels\n- Poor anger management\n- Impulsive personality\n- Feeling anonymous while driving\n- Sense of competition or territorialism\n\n2. Environmental triggers\n- Heavy traffic\n- Running late\n- Long commutes\n- Aggressive driving by others\n- Perceived disrespect or discourtesy from other drivers\n\n3. Emotional contributors\n- Frustration\n- Feeling powerless or out of control\n- Perceived personal insult\n- Lack of empathy for other drivers\n- Previous negative driving experiences\n\n4. Personal factors\n- Low tolerance for frustration\n- History of violent behavior\n- Mental health issues\n- Substance abuse\n- Lack of sleep or fatigue\n\n5. Situational elements\n- Personal problems or life stressors\n- Time pressure\n- Anonymity of being in a vehicle\n- Cultural attitudes toward driving\n\n6. Biological factors\n- Hormonal changes\n- Testosterone levels\n- Genetic predisposition to aggression\n\nAddressing road rage often involves developing better emotional regulation, stress management techniques, and maintaining a more patient, empathetic attitude while driving.",
